          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "32-GE-76",
                "field_identifier": "NAT",
                "value": 0.0773
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Two disks, about 0.1 and 0.19",
                "cm in thickness and 20 mm in diameter, were formed by",
                "pressing approximately 1.7 and 3.2 g of Ge (99.99%",
                "pure) powder (natural isotopic composition) at 980 MPa",
                "to form a pellet. The samples were irradiated near",
                "the target and sandwiched between two Nb foils (99.99%",
                "pure, 0.12 mm thick) with the same diameter which",
                "were used to monitor the neutron fluence via the",
                "93Nb(n,2n)92mNb reaction."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-T"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Neutrons were produced with an effective",
                "deuteron beam energy of 135 keV, beam current of 240",
                "uA, and the diameter of the deuteron beam spot was",
                "under 0.6 cm. The samples were centered a 0.566 mg/cm2",
                "thick T-Mo target at a distance of about 50 mm. The",
                "diameter of the active zone of the T-Mo target is 1.2",
                "cm."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The measurements were carried out using low-",
                "background high-purity germanium detector (ORTEC,",
                "model GEM 60P, crystal diameter 70.1 mm, crystal",
                "length 72.3 mm) with a relative efficiency of about",
                "68% and an energy resolution of 1.69 keV at 1.332 MeV",
                "for Co-60. The detector was pre-calibrated for energy",
                "and efficiency by using the standard gamma ray",
                "sources Mn-54, Co-57, Co-60, Cd-109, Ba-133, Cs-137,",
                "Eu-152, Am-241 and Ra-226. The distance from sample",
                "to detector was 2.0 cm."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The Au-Si surface barrier detector used in",
                "alpha-particle tube was positioned at 135 degree and",
                "110 cm from the target."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Irradiation of the samples was lasted",
                "approximately 3 minutes with a neutron yield 3 to",
                "4E10 n/s in 4pi solid angle. The groups of samples",
                "were placed at 0, 90, and 135 degree relative to the",
                "beam direction. During irradiation, the neutron flux",
                "was monitored by accompanying alpha-particles so that",
                "corrections could be made for small variations of the",
                "yield."
              ]
            }
          ],
